The paper discusses a novel algorithm for data clustering that achieves linear time computational complexity, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of hash tables and partial-signature keys suggests that the paper may belong to the data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), or database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The benchmark measurements on clustering news articles by topic suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
